The [[Most Reverend|Most Rev]] '''John Lyons''', [[Doctor of Divinity|DD]] (29 November 1878 - 11 June 1958)<ref> The Times, Monday, Jun 16, 1958; pg. 13; Issue 54178; col B ''News in Brief''</ref>
was [[Anglican Diocese of Ontario|Bishop of Ontario]] <ref>[[Crockford's clerical directory|Crockford's Clerical Directory]] 1940/41 Oxford, [[OUP]], 1940</ref>, then [[Ecclesiastical Province of Ontario|Metropolitan of Ontario]] <ref>[http://www2.anglican.ca/search/faq/024.htm Metropolitans of Ontario]</ref> in the 20th century.<br> Educated at [[Trinity College, Toronto]], he was the  [[Vicar|incumbent]] at [[Plevna, Ontario|Plevna]] and then [[Rector]] of [[Burritts Rapids, Ontario|Burritt<U+2019>s Rapids]]. He held further posts at [[Elizabethtown-Kitley, Ontario|Elizabethtown]], [[Picton, Ontario|Picton]], [[Belleville, Ontario|Belleville]] and [[Prescott, Ontario|Prescott]]. He was appointed [[Archdeacon]] of [[Frontenac]] in 1930 and Anglican Diocese of Ontario|Bishop of Ontario]] in 1932; and for his last three years in office (1949 to 1952) [[Metropolitan of Ontario]]. 
